article.description: Doyle leads Loyola Chicago past Campbell 80-68
article.headline: Doyle leads Loyola Chicago past Campbell 80-68
article.linkText: Doyle leads Loyola Chicago past Campbell 80-68
article.story: CHICAGO -- Milton Doyle scored 21 of his game-high 32 points in the second half to lead Loyola of Chicago to an 80-68 win over Campbell Friday night. Loyola trailed by one at halftime and the Fighting Camels extended their lead to six, 40-34 on three straight 3-pointers, two by Reco McCarter. The Ramblers grabbed the lead at 46-43 on a 3-pointer by Matt O'Leary with 14:55 left and never looked back. Doyle was 9 of 13 from the field and 12 of 15 from the free throw line to lead Loyola Chicago and help put the game away from the line, sandwiching six straight free throws around a layup in the final 2:16. Christian Thomas added 16 points and O'Leary added 15 point off the bench. McCarter and Luke Moyer each scored 12 points to lead Campbell, with Darius Leonard adding another 11.
